# APR - Automated Program Repair

A multi-agent system for automated program repair and code generation using large language models.

## Installation

### From source (development mode)

```bash
git clone https://github.com/kaushithamsilva/APR.git
cd APR

# Install the package with human-eval dependency
pip install -e .

# Note: The human-eval package will be automatically installed from GitHub
# If you have a local copy in ./human-eval/, you can also install it separately:
# pip install -e ./human-eval/
```

### With optional dependencies

```bash
# For development
pip install -e ".[dev]"

# For notebooks
pip install -e ".[notebooks]"

# For OpenAI support
pip install -e ".[openai]"

# All dependencies
pip install -e ".[dev,notebooks,openai]"
```

### Human-Eval Dependency

This project depends on the [human-eval](https://github.com/openai/human-eval) package for code evaluation. You have two options:

1. **Automatic installation** (recommended): The human-eval package will be installed automatically from GitHub when you install this package.

2. **Local installation**: If you have a local copy of human-eval in your project:

   ```bash
   pip install -e ./human-eval/
   ```

## Quick Start

```python
# Import the main components
from apr import CodeProcessor, LLMClient

# Initialize components
processor = CodeProcessor()
client = LLMClient("ollama", "qwen2.5-coder:7b")

# Use them in your code
problem = '''def factorial(n: int) -> int:
    """Calculate factorial of n."""
    pass'''

function_name = processor.extract_function_name_from_prompt(problem)
print(f"Function name: {function_name}")
```

## Project Structure

```
src/
├── common/              # Shared utilities
│   ├── code_processor.py
│   ├── llm_client.py
│   └── config.py
└── agentcoder_plus/     # AgentCoder+ implementation
    ├── agents/
    ├── memory/
    └── workflows/
```

